annotationA: Transcription initiation factor IIA subunit 1; TFIIA is a component of the transcription machinery of RNA polymerase II and plays an important role in transcriptional activation. TFIIA in a complex with TBP mediates transcriptional activity; Belongs to the TFIIA subunit 1 family
annotationB: CDK7/cyclin H assembly factor MAT1; RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity; zinc ion binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cell cycle; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
